com.datamirror.ts.derivedexpressionmanager

Class UserExitInvokeException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.datamirror.ts.derivedexpressionmanager.UserExitInvokeException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class UserExitInvokeException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown in the DEUserExitIF.invoke(Object[])method to indicate that an error has been encountered during execution of the method. If this exception is thrown, and no result is returned to the %USER function, a message will generated and logged indicating that the expression containing the %USER function call could not be evaluated.
